## 9. WRITING INSTRUCTIONS

**Post gen instruction:** Follow these writing rules for every paragraph of body copy.

- This is conversion copy — every sentence moves the buyer toward a purchase decision.
- Lead with buyer benefit ("won't crack your acrylic"), not specs ("stainless steel blade") — specs support the benefit, never lead with it.
- Use buyer phrases from Section 3/5 naturally — speak their language, paraphrased, never copied verbatim from review sources.
- Address all 5 buying objections from Section 5 directly — no hedging.
- Be honest about the spring/cap complaints found in research; counter with why the Rotary Adjustable Clippers (highest-rated, 4.9/64 reviews) is the safer default recommendation.
- Place discount information (MSOFF15, free shipping threshold, 65%-off kit) near CTAs, not as standalone paragraphs.
- Wrap every mention of **MelodySusie nail clippers** in `<strong>` tags — no exceptions.
- No editorial literary hooks — open each H2 with the buyer benefit or buying question directly.
- Keep H2 sections short and direct — buyers scan, they do not read long intros.
- Conclusion is a final push to purchase, not a summary.
- Place internal links from Section 1 mid-post only, after the first product CTA — anchor text natural, never forced.
- No related articles section — handled by site component.
- American English throughout — not British English.
- No banned AI patterns: no "elevate," "seamlessly," "game-changing," "dive into," "transformative."
- No long em dashes — use commas or restructure.
- Vary sentence rhythm — short punchy sentences for key selling points, longer sentences for context.
- The 4-in-1 kits and 3-in-1 kit have zero or near-zero reviews (4-in-1s: 0 reviews; 3-in-1: 3 reviews) — use informed editorial observation language for these, not "we tested" language. Example tone: "The 4 in 1 Kit is built for buyers who want cutting and cuticle care in one purchase — its U-shaped adjustable blade and razor-sharp cuticle nipper make it a strong pick for anyone setting up a full at-home nail station without buying tools separately."
